Heads up! We're now ON DECK for Vox.<br>
<br>
Please state your name, class, level, guild, unbuffed cold and magic resists, and list what experience you have battling this dragon (e.g. pulled, buff circle...). We will most likely limit the minimum level selected to 45 for melees and 49 for casters, but do sign up anyway if you aren't quite there. Of course, the maximum level allowed is 52.<br>
<br>
Those above level 52 who wish to assist in buffing, please sign up as well. It helps immensely in the preparation for battle. Preference for any slots go first to our guild and our allies, needed classes, then those from this sign up.<br>
<br>
It will be fun!<br>
<br>
<br>
LOOT Rules for Vox<br>
---------------------<br>
<br>
This is our version of Vox loot rules.<br>
<br>
Violent Harvest is claiming the second of any item that drops. <br>
<br>
The paladin book will be rolled on by paladins only. Should two books drop, Violent Harvest reserves the right to award the second book to whomever it chooses of the remaining paladins.<br>
<br>
We support those who endeavor for epic quests, and thus, if one White Dragon Scale drops, it will be rolled on by bards only. If two drop, one will be rolled on by bards only and the other rolled on by remaining bards and the appropriate casters (both INT and WIS). It is encouraged that if a caster wins the second scale, they allow one of the bards to trade them a white scale or heirophant cloak in exchange for the scale.<br>
<br>
Karvuul's Pouch - Monks who offer a tinkerer's bag in exchange will be able to roll first. Then the tinkerer's bag will be rolled on by all.<br>
<br>
Tobrin's Mystical Eyepatch will only be rolled on by casters (both INT and WIS).<br>
<br>
Crystalline Spear - WAR RNG BRD ROG only to roll.<br>
<br>
Runed Bolster Belt - melee classes only to roll on this.<br>
<br>
Staff of the Forbidden Rites - will be open to all to roll on for the resurrection proc available.<br>
<br>
Dragon Bone Bracer - WAR PAL RNG SK MNK BRD ROG only.<br>
<br>
Warhammer of Divine Grace - Cleric Only.<br>
<br>
McVaxius' Horn of War - Bard Only.<br>
<br>
Other epic pieces - rolled on by classes who can use, eg. Block of Pemafrost or Prickly Pear.<br>
<br>
Note: Higher level players that we've invited to help clear the way to the lair will be allowed to participate in rolls should they choose to.<br>
<br>
Group captains will be the only ones looting the kills along the way. Any questions about loot and the loot rules should be directed to me before the raid starts. <br>
<br>
Upon Vox's death, everyone will back away from the corpse. The group leader will look at Vox's corpse and report what is on her. Only the Raid Leader will actually loot rollable items. If paladin books are on her, they will be randomed first. <br>
<br>
Selilya Withertouch <br>
Winnower of the Violent Harvest <br>
Devoted Daughter of Innoruuk <br>
